social_posts.post_text: One of the greatest joys of my life is being her mom and making memories with her. Dreamy Nutcracker night. 🩰🎄
What a year. 🥹✨

✨ O N E ✨ 

One year ago… you swept into the world just in time to kiss me at midnight. Your peaceful, gentle demeanor eased us into being a family of five and we love seeing you grow into the mischievous, adorable guy you’re becoming. Happy birthday, Graham Warren. You’re the perfectly fitting piece to our family puzzle. What an honor it is to be yours. 😭

Recently I’ve found that afternoon cup of coffee tastes better in a fancy tea cup. 

Maybe it’s the reminder that we can really just have beautiful little moments in the mundane wearing our child-stained sweatshirts and a few day old messy bun…

The moments in between meals and putting in another load— drop offs, pick ups and “mom have you seen my ______”…

The days spent pouring and pouring all we have into these ones under our roofs while we have them here… and we do it because we love it and them more than words can say and because this is holy, beautiful work…

So when I feel the day swirling yet the years slipping sometimes I just need to sit and recount the goodness of who God is and the goodness of the days I’m living… and count the beautiful little gifts just here under my roof. And I’m finding this works best with an afternoon cup of coffee in a fancy tea cup.
January 2023 🤟🏼

Happy birthday to our full-of-life four year old. You are fun and joy wrapped up into one and you keep this family light and laughing. Life-of-the-party should’ve been your middle name but we’ll never think of you otherwise. Happiest day to you, Van Abram. If I could freeze you at this age forever I would, but since I can’t… it’s my joy to watch you grow and become all God made you to be. We love you forever bubba.
February 🤍

Within the past week she lost her two front teeth. At first I was strong as I watched the joy spill out of her before bed and I tucked in that little gapped-tooth beauty who was riding on cloud nine… but as the sound of her voice changed with the saying of her “sssss”, and remembering those two little teef that kept us up in the night as they weaseled their way through… I haven’t been strong. Sitting in the midst of joy and grief as I watch the little-ness pass like the winter fading behind us. This is what we were made for, right? This is why I’m here? To care for and watch them flourish. To become all God made them to be. To encourage, nurture and cheer them on as they grow and change and prepare them for such a time as this but today I’m wanting to stop this train and sit with this little-ness a little longer. Oh the joy of motherhood. The joy of motherhood with a dash of longing and releasing… may I just sit here a little longer…
Based on true events. (Don’t worry to my friends, not real time events).

Seven. Seven years of bliss with you. To you opening something within me that I only could’ve dreamed of existing. Seven years of your joy, peace, and sparkle… compassion, patience and absolute FUN. Seven years of you teaching me the significance of taking life slow— and you teach me to stop and smell the roses on the way. You never miss an opportunity to point out beauty and you embody it in full. You, my darling girl, are a dream come true. Happy birthday to my bright eyed, angel baby. You are my treasure.

T E N 

Ten years ago, that one-day-from-21 year old girl was the surest in her whole life that she wanted to spend the rest of her life with you… and ten years later, out of all the unsure, you’ve remained the surest. Everyday with you has been a gift, @paulwhittinghill. Here’s to allll the decades to come. I love you and our life together. Happy Anniversary, babe. 🥹🫶🏼
